The "context state word" feature (claude/yas/context_state.py) — the idea of a
morphing Smart -> Coasting -> Foggy -> Cooked -> Dumb label driven by context
fullness, together with the default labels and 25/50/70/90 thresholds — is
ported from Dumbometer's level model (src/config.js) and label-selection logic
(src/state.js). YAS adapts it to map the word off its soft-limit fill ratio
rather than the full context-window percentage.

